The Color Palette
ðŸ”µ Blue (Keywords)

Hex: #61AFEF (Soft Blue)

Usage: const, let, function, require

Why: It draws the eye to the structure of the logic.

ðŸŸ¢ Green (Strings)

Hex: #98C379 (Sage Green)

Usage: '10.1.0.40', '/home/pi/script.sh'

Why: Green is distinct from blue/white so you can instantly see where text data starts and ends.

ðŸŸ£ Purple (Numbers & Booleans)

Hex: #C678DD (Lavender)

Usage: 1, 0, true, false, return

Why: These are "hard" values or exit points, so they get a bold, contrasting color.

âšª Whitish (Variables & Text)

Hex: #ABB2BF (Light Gray/White)

Usage: myAtem, console, wasRecording

Why: This is the default color for the names you create. It is soft on the eyes for reading lists of variables.

ðŸŒ« Gray (Comments)

Hex: #7F848E (Slate Gray)

Usage: // This is a comment

Why: It is low-contrast so it recedes into the background. You only read it if you are looking for it.

Background Color
To make those colors pop correctly, you usually need a dark gray background:

Background: #282C34 (Dark Blue-Gray)
